OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA grey start for most with some
OL,6,Fhill fog and the odd spot of drizzle.
OL,7,FHowever, cloud gradually lifting and
OL,8,Fbreaking to give some brighter
OL,9,Fafternoon spells, feeling warmer than
OL,10,FSunday. Mostly dry, although isolated
OL,11,Flight showers possible. Light winds.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FVariable cloud and some clear
OL,14,Fspells. Mostly dry, although a few
OL,15,Fshowers reaching the far north towards
OL,16,Fdawn. Turning chilly in some rural
OL,17,Fspots, with winds remaining light.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
